description.0: The origin of Johnny Blaze! After making a deal with the devil for the soul of his adoptive father, stunt motorcyclist Johnny Blaze is transformed into the Spirit of Vengeance, actual servant to Satan!
description.1: The Hulk must battle...his own shadow? Meanwhile, more shady business unravels at the Hulkbuster Base in New Mexico.
description.2: Firelord attacks the God of Thunder! And the puppetmaster pulling Firelord's strings is none other than Loki!
description.3: A ravenous and mad Dracula takes another female victim! Taj reflects on the night of his son's vampiric transformation.
description.4: Blade, Vampire Hunter, begins his quest to take down endless legions of the UNLIVING DEAD!
description.5: The Silver Surfer, familiar compatriot of the FF, is back- but not as a friend. The tormented Surfer is battling with his heart vs. his conscience. Will slaying the Fantastic Four free his love, Shalla-Bal, from the clutches of Doctor Doom?
description.9: Who is Adam Warlock? Let's find out more about the Man who Stalked the Stars in his definitive origin! Plus, the history of the High Evolutionary's Counter-Earth!
description.10: In search for a fix to his malfunctioning suit, "Multiple Man" returns to New York City and battles the Fantastic Four.
description.16: John Kowalski faces that which he once welcomed and feared-Death, personified
description.17: LEARNING CURVE PART 2! ELSA BLOODSTONE IS MISSING! When KID KAIJU’s mentor goes missing, he will have to use all of his wits – and his knowledge of monster lore – to track her down and save the day. There is something in the deep, dark ocean, something ancient and terrible, long slumbering and now awake…and it’s HUNGRY!
description.18: The final undoing of the Caretakers of Arcturus!
description.19: The return of Mysterio! Meet the second incarnation of Spider-Man's most dastardly villain. How is Mysterio back from the dead? And what is this new Mysterio's connection to the Daily Bugle?
description.20: The Celestial Madonna is Mantis! The Avengers are still stuck in the realm of Limbo, with the newly-formed Legion of the Unliving. This legion consists of villainous foes past and present who have been resurrected by Immortus.
description.21: See the man called Nomad trapped in an inferno! Plus, the end of the sinister Serpent Squad!
description.23: Maura Spinner's history unfolds aboard an ancient ship. Man-Thing engages in a piratical battle!
description.27: Valkyrie joins the fight alongside Thing and Dr. Strange to battle evil magic as well as Executioner and the Enchantress!
description.28: The Gamma Bomb goes missing and it's a race to find it between the Defenders and the Wrecking Crew!
description.29: Captain Marvel is back on Earth! Why has he returned?
description.32: Bruce lands a job as a scientist in Chicago! When an experiment goes awry, Zzzax is summoned, absorbing the intellect and feelings of scientist Stan Landers. Will Bruce choose his new life over saving the city of Chicago?
description.33: Tony Stark finds himself in grave danger when Whiplash, the Melter, and the Man-Bull attack! Together you can call them Death Squad! Extra: the maddening menace of the Black Lama!
description.34: The spirit of Armak arrears to cause problems for the God of Thunder. Plus, will Jane Foster recover from her injuries?
description.35: Taj Nitall must reach a difficult decision about his newly-transformed son. Dr. Sun continues to abuse his thrall over the Chimera statue.
description.36: Reed, Johnny and Ben are attacked by the Mystery Villain- but how? In a series of flashbacks, the team recalls Reed disguising himself as the shrouded figure in the past. Who can this Mystery Villain be? There's only one way to find out...
description.38: The Jackal and Grizzly kidnap Peter to uncover Spider-Man's civilian identity. Rigged with a tracking device set to explode upon its removal, Peter wonders if he can ever again become Spider-Man. Plus, J. Jonah Jameson reveals why Grizzly has beef with the Bugle!
description.39: The Avengers remain in Vietnam to help Mantis discover more secrets about her mysterious origins. Meanwhile, in the realm of Limbo, demon lord Immortus has rescued Kang and Rama-Tut from the time stream. Back on earth, Mantis is visited by an astral form of Swordsman, which leaves her both confused and scared.
description.40: With Steve Rogers as the Nomad, will another don the Captain America costume? Find out the secret identity of the new Captain America!
description.44: PANTHER'S RAGE PART 8: The Panther goes up against the White Gorilla, which most Wakandans considered to be a myth! Contains only "The God Killer" story.
description.49: Man-Thing takes an accidental voyage to the Bermuda Triangle!
description.54: Daredevil and the Defenders are chosen by Grandmaster to be the latest pawns in his cosmic game. Will the heroes play to win?
description.55: If Man-Wolf claims Kristine Saunders's life, the blood will be on John Jameson's hands! The werewolf edges towards disaster when he targets one of his closest friends…
description.59: Captain America! Sub-Mariner! The Human Torch! The fiercest Allies from World War II unite in battle against the Axis of evil that is destabilizing the world at large!
description.62: The devastation of the Wrecking Crew continues! Plus, the introduction of a Gamma Bomb raises the stakes!
description.66: Roxanne is seduced by a satanic offer. In his Ghost Rider form, Johnny Blaze discovers a vulnerability that may possess his soul.
description.67: Hulk befriends homeless man Crackerjack Jackson in the wilds of Canada. What will happen when Jackson is reunited with his long lost son, Johnny Anvil?
description.68: Guest-starring the Prince of Power himself, Hercules! Can Thor stop a mad-with-rage Hercules?
description.69: Dr. Sun places the Lord of Vampires in a deathtrap for the remaining fragments of the Chimera statue!
description.70: Blade, human/vampire hybrid, stars in his first ever appearance! Meet the Slayer of the Undead and learn his incredible origin!
description.75: Peter finds a new apartment in Chelsea, but quickly realizes he needs to bolster his income for rent. Soon after taking his job back at the Bugle, the office is attacked by a costumed wrestler called "the Grizzly." Who is this new costumed menace? And will Peter be able to become Spider-Man in time to save the day?
description.76: The Avengers return to Vietnam to bury the body of their fallen teammate Swordsman, with the Priests of Pama. However, their trip takes an unexpected turn when the team is greeted by three old enemies; Radioactive Man, Crimson Dynamo, and Titanium Man!
description.77: The First Appearance of Steve Rogers as Nomad. The end of Captain America! The awesome origin of Steve Rogers' new identity! Look out evil wrong-doers! Here comes the Nomad!
description.78: A tortured writer is haunted by his creditors. Sybil Mills attempts to assuage the writer's doubts, but Man-Thing offers Brian Lazarus the relief he needs.
description.86: A town bands together to kill Dracula before his next meal!
description.88: John Kowalski takes on the body of Dr. Bock to help his family get away during Germany's Polish occupation.
description.89: Martine Bancroft is Michael Morbius’ first love… but this romance threatens to end in a pool of blood.
description.90: Thing and Dr. Strange team-up to battle mystic threats attacking Manhattan!
description.92: The Defenders get a little help from Luke Cage, Power Man, to go toe-to-toe with the destruction of the Wrecking Crew!
description.94: Annihilus has taken Captain Marvel under his control!
description.95: Peter laments over his totaled apartment following Spider-Man's battle with Green Goblin. Although invited to stay with Flash Thompson, Peter reconsiders when he finds out Flash lives in faraway Queens! Plus, the introduction of Mindworm, a strange mutant with the ability to manipulate emotion.
description.96: Kang appears at the Avengers Mansion seeking a woman who is known as the "Celestial Madonna". One of the two women at the Mansion will be the Madonna that Kang must "sire an heir with." The rest of the team decides to defend Mantis and Scarlet Witch by warding off Kang's overtly creepy advances.
description.97: Captain America may be the champion of liberty, but is Steve Rogers a match for the Golden Archer?
description.99: The awesome Armored Avenger face to face with the world's great super-villians! And it all begins now!

6.text: Glory Grant is in danger! Spidey and Falcon must engage in mortal combat against the mysterious Midas!

7.text: The terror of tarot! An impromptu card reading for Daimon goes awry when the spirits of the cards come to life and attack!

11.text: The truth is out! Kung Fu legend Shang-Chi stars in ‘A Contest of Truth’!

12.text: Luke Cage discovers Security City, an armed compound where xenophobia rules and conforming is essential to survive.

13.text: Shang-Chi, Sir Denis and Black Jack Tarr have managed to keep Fu Manchu from getting his hands on a nuclear weapon, but they now face a long walk home through the remote wilderness of the Amazon…where a tribe of brutal headhunters are sure to complicate things!

22.text: The Man-Thing is transported to the realm between day and night to help Korrek fend off the evil forces threatening his home!

23.text: Maura Spinner's history unfolds aboard an ancient ship. Man-Thing engages in a piratical battle!

24.text: Buck gets his hands on Redditch’s “good formula”, and Jack chugs the mixture!

25.text: Deathlok wanders far from the land he calls home to find Simon Ryker and kill him. However, Ryker is able to foresee Deathlok’s arrival and sends out armored tanks to defeat his creation-gone-rogue.

26.text: Iron Fist finds himself (again), under the attack of the Cult of Kara-Kai. Will Fist ever be able to clear his name with Joy Meachum? Uncle Ward Meachum calls in a big gun to eliminate Iron Fist…Batroc the Leaper! Plus, what does Lee Wing have that the Ninja wants for himself?

27.text: Valkyrie joins the fight alongside Thing and Dr. Strange to battle evil magic as well as Executioner and the Enchantress!

28.text: The Gamma Bomb goes missing and it's a race to find it between the Defenders and the Wrecking Crew!

29.text: Captain Marvel is back on Earth! Why has he returned?

31.text: Defeated, Daredevil and Black Widow become prisoners of the Owl…who plans to mind-wipe Matt!

41.text: Shang-Chi and the Sons of the Tiger return in a back-to-back action packed tale!

42.text: Werewolf by Night finds himself in deadly danger - deep in the heart of TRANSYLVANIA! Plus, classic tales of Marvel horror throughout the ages!

43.text: When Sir Denis Nayland asks for an audience with Shang-Chi, the two get wrapped up in unraveling Fu Manchu's plot to collaborate with a former Gestapo agent!

44.text: Contains only "The God Killer" story. PANTHER’S RAGE PART 8: The Panther goes up against the White Gorilla, which most Wakandans considered to be a myth!

45.text: Spider-Man receives a call for help in Morse code…but fears he may have walked into a trap!

48.text: Frankenstein’s Monster vs. a being more terrifying than himself! The Night-Creature hunts his prey expertly, giving the Monster a violent display of power. Janice Caccone’s in grave danger.

49.text: Man-Thing takes an accidental voyage to the Bermuda Triangle!

50.text: After putting Redditch in a coma, can Jack convince the scientist to allow him to try his formula to cure him of his lycanthropy?

52.text: Iron Man needs help and summons the Fantastic Four -- but for some reason, only the Torch bothers to show up!

53.text: A series of stories featuring America's greatest crime destroyer, The Punisher!

57.text: Kem Horkus has asked Ka-Zar's help in seeking revenge against the one who betrayed his family!

58.text: The Death Breeders, hot in pursuit of human experiments Adam 3,031 and Eve 3,031, fall to the might of Killraven and his freedom fighters!

59.text: Captain America! Sub-Mariner! The Human Torch! The fiercest Allies from World War II unite in battle against the Axis of evil that is destabilizing the world at large!

61.text: Silver Dagger reveals his origin to Clea!

62.text: The devastation of the Wrecking Crew continues! Plus, the introduction of a Gamma Bomb raises the stakes!

65.text: After a cryptic phone call from Natasha, Daredevil travels to San Francisco and finds her missing from her mansion!

71.text: Peter Parker and Hercules partner up when Manhattan is shaken by a supposedly-impossible earthquake.

72.text: Daimon Hellstrom continues his showdown with the demon Allatou - with an entire family's lives in the balance! The Son of Satan's only hope is to make the demon an offer she can't refuse!

74.text: Deathlok takes on War-Wolf! In a future where warfare is accomplished through genetically modified soldiers, will Deathlok prove the supreme “super soldier” of them all? Plus, who was War-Wolf before his transformation, and what ties does he have to Deathlok’s past?

78.text: A tortured writer is haunted by his creditors. Sybil Mills attempts to assuage the writer's doubts, but Man-Thing offers Brian Lazarus the relief he needs.

79.text: Jack and Buck head to the home of scientist Winston Redditch, whom they believe can help Jack with a special Jekyll and Hyde formula the scientist has “perfected”…

80.text: Kung Fu double feature! Join Shang-Chi, the Master of Kung Fu in “The Past Assasins” and the Sons of the Tiger in “Tigers in a Mind-Cage!”

81.text: Luke has to face Stiletto, but this time he has a new partner in crime...Discus!

82.text: When a drunk outside a martial arts studio accosts Shang-Chi one night, the Master of Kung Fu throws the man through a window. But this studio is owned by Sandy, a beautiful woman who can hold her own in a fistfight. But falling for Sandy has its downsides -- namely, giving Fu Manchu and his army of assassins the ultimate leverage over Shang-Chi!

83.text: When Sir Denis Nayland asks for an audience with Shang-Chi, the two get wrapped up in unraveling Fu Manchu's plot to collaborate with a former Gestapo agent!

90.text: Thing and Dr. Strange team-up to battle mystic threats attacking Manhattan!

91.text: The Avengers, hurtled through time at the hands of Kang! Earth’s Mightiest Heroes find themselves neck-deep in a rescue mission…in ancient Egypt! Will Thor, Iron Man, and Vision be saved from Kang’s Macrobots? A revelation about Mantis’ true identity tears the time stream in two.  An Avenger falls in battle.

92.text: The Defenders get a little help from Luke Cage, Power Man, to go toe-to-toe with the destruction of the Wrecking Crew!

93.text: The trap has been set and Iron Fist is the prey! Joy Meachum lays the groundwork for her plot against Iron Fist. The Ninja bursts back into Daniel Rand’s life bearing really bad news. And what is the Cult of Kara-Kai?

94.text: Annihilus has taken Captain Marvel under his control!

98.text: Daredevil returns to New York to rescue Foggy and Candace, and once again finds himself facing Death-Stalker!
